  <wpt lat="41.202167" lon="-96.031383">
    <time>2026-03-08T13:45:00</time>
    <name>GCBJJVE</name>
    <desc>Pre Pi Day Mystery Solving Quest by LadyCache, Event Cache (1.0/1.0)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBJJVE</url>
    <urlname>Pre Pi Day Mystery Solving Quest</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10301967" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>Pre Pi Day Mystery Solving Quest</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>LadyCache</groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="568858">LadyCache</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="0">Horses</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="0">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="64" inc="0">Tree climbing required</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.0</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;08 March 2026, 13:45 - 16:15&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;p&gt;Pi Day is back, and this year&amp;rsquo;s celebration is about more than a clever number; it&amp;rsquo;s a full-on Mystery Cache quest. Earn up to 3 Pi Day 2026 souvenirs by finding and logging Mystery Caches between March 13-15, 2026.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Let&amp;#39;s combine team forces to solve some Mystery puzzles to plot our quest during the Pi Day Challenge!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We will be in one of the meeting rooms at&amp;nbsp;Baright Public Library,&amp;nbsp;5555 South 77 St,&amp;nbsp;Ralston, NE 68127.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Sunday, March 8, 2026&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; The room is reserved from 1:30 pm - 4:30 pm, and the event is from 1:45 pm - 4:15 pm to allow a little time for set up and take down of the tables and chairs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;About this event (no souvenir - but you will be armed ready for the Pi Day Challenge!)&lt;img alt="yes" height="23" src="https://imgproxy.geocaching.com/cd69b0c9b98bb39781fd2287d7c215b73562a54a/68747470733a2f2f63646e2e636b656469746f722e636f6d2f342e32322e312f66756c6c2d616c6c2f706c7567696e732f736d696c65792f696d616765732f7468756d62735f75702e706e67" title="yes" width="23" /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;An event about solving puzzles for all of us who are puzzled by all these puzzles.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Please list GC code(s) for puzzles you would like to work on in your &amp;quot;Will Attend Log&amp;quot;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Perhaps you have a hint to help someone else.&amp;nbsp; Maybe you will meet the cache owner that placed the geocache that has stumped you.&amp;nbsp; The intent is to pool our brain power to solve geocache puzzles.&amp;nbsp; There is no limit on the geographic location nor difficulty level of the geocache we will consider.&amp;nbsp; Bring your secret tools to help others. Feel free to bring along your laptop, tablet, or phone.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A list of puzzles will be posted that we will focus on as a group a couple days prior to the event.&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bring snacks and drinks if you want (no alcohol, sorry, library rules)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can&amp;#39;t stay the whole time, that&amp;#39;s ok. Stop by and say hi or provide a few puzzle solving tibits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Come have some fun and help solve some puzzles!&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This year&amp;rsquo;s Pi Day celebration comes with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;tiered souvenirs&lt;/strong&gt;. That means you can earn up to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;3 souvenirs&lt;/strong&gt;, depending on how many&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Mystery Caches&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;you find and log between March 13-15, 2026.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Between March 13-15, 2026, earn 3 Pi Day 2026 souvenirs:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Find and log&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mystery Cache to earn the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Coconut Cream Pi souvenir&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Find and log&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;3&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mystery Caches to earn the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Cherry Pi souvenir&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Find and log&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;14&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Mystery Caches to earn the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Blueberry Pi souvenir&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;a href="http://nebraskache.com/"&gt;&lt;img height="112" src="https://img.geocaching.com/9102f957-c986-41b5-acdb-a076bd017129.jpg" width="224" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;a href="http://nebraskache.com/"&gt;Hosted By A Nebraskache Member&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/107321656812/"&gt;&lt;img height="68" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/19b6196d-f1d8-431b-9201-f4069d107ada_l.png" width="213" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center"&gt;As the geocache event owner, I ensure that these links to a local geocaching group that is active in the community and contributing to geocaching in positive ways. This link has not been checked by Geocaching HQ or by the reviewer.&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
      <groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      </groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      <groundspeak:logs>
        <groundspeak:log id="1345790253">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-02-21T17:53:12Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Will Attend</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="1720574">Grumble69</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Hoping to attend. Puzzles are my preferred thing.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
